This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney during a two-day, multi-state trip focusing on American-made energy and the President's all-of-the-above approach to energy needs and challenges. Carney discusses various topics including the administration's authority over the Keystone pipeline, tariffs on solar panels from China, Republican criticism of the President's stance on drilling, the upcoming NATO summit, the United Nations' support for Kofi Annan's efforts in Syria, and the President's vote in the Illinois primary. Carney also mentions that the President is confident in the constitutionality of the individual responsibility provision within the Affordable Care Act.